==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Ineffective
<hw>In`ef*fect"ive</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>in-</ets> not + <ets>effective</ets>: cf. F.
<ets>ineffectif</ets>.]</ety> <def>Not effective; not having the desired
effect; ineffectual; futile; inefficient; useless; <as>as, an
<ex>ineffective</ex> appeal; an <ex>ineffective</ex> herbal
remedy</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><q>The word of God, without the spirit, [is] a dead and
<qex>ineffective</qex> letter.</q> <rj><qau>Jer. Taylor.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ineffectively</ent>⟦br⟧
